Interface Cardinality<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type returned by all methods of this interface - for onward call chaining.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Check<C,R>, ClassCheck<C>, ClassExpectation<T>, Expectation<E,R>, LambdaCheck<R>, LambdaExpectation<R>, ObjectCheck<T>, ObjectExpectation<T>

    public interface Cardinality<T>
    Domain-specific language methods used to specify how many times an event (method call, sequence of method calls) is expected to occur.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T anyTimes()
      The related event may occur any number of times, if it occurs at all.
      T atLeast(int times)
      The related event should occur at least times times.
      T atLeastOnce()
      The related event should occur one or more times.
      T atMost(int times)
      The related event should occur at most times times, if at all.
      T atMostOnce()
      The related event should occur exactly once, if at all.
      T never()
      The related event should never occur.
      T once()
      The related event should occur exactly one time.
      T times(int times)
      The related event should occur exactly times times.
      T times(int minTimes, int maxTimes)
      The related event should occur between minTimes and maxTimes times, inclusive.
